## Overview
Implement the `packages/data` package: drift SQLite schema, migrations, and concrete implementations of the repository interfaces defined in `packages/domain`.

## Depends on
- while-youre-out-3r5 (domain package — repository interfaces and entities must be defined)

## Package location
`packages/data/`

## pubspec.yaml
Already scaffolded in while-youre-out-qys. Run `dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs` after creating table definitions to generate drift code.

## Database (lib/src/database/app_database.dart)

```dart
import 'dart:io';
import 'package:drift/drift.dart';
import 'package:drift/native.dart';
import 'package:path/path.dart' as p;
import 'package:path_provider/path_provider.dart';

part 'app_database.g.dart';

@DriftDatabase(tables: [TodoListsTable, TodoItemsTable, GeofenceRegionsTable])
class AppDatabase extends _$AppDatabase {
  AppDatabase() : super(_openConnection());
  AppDatabase.forTesting(super.connection);  // allows NativeDatabase.memory() in tests

  @override
  int get schemaVersion => 1;

  @override
  MigrationStrategy get migration => MigrationStrategy(
    onCreate: (m) => m.createAll(),
    onUpgrade: (m, from, to) async {
      // add future migrations here
    },
  );
}

LazyDatabase _openConnection() {
  return LazyDatabase(() async {
    final dbFolder = await getApplicationDocumentsDirectory();
    final file = File(p.join(dbFolder.path, 'while_youre_out.db'));
    if (Platform.isIOS) {
      // Exclude from iCloud backup
      // Use NSFileManager via platform channel OR dart:io File setAttributes workaround
      // Simplest approach: write a small method channel call in apps/mobile to set
      // NSURLIsExcludedFromBackupKey — document this as a TODO for Phase 2 iOS native work
    }
    return NativeDatabase.createInBackground(file);
  });
}
```

**Note on iCloud exclusion**: The cleanest implementation is a platform channel call from `apps/mobile` after the DB file is created — document this as a TODO comment in `_openConnection()`. The actual exclusion can be wired in the Phase 2 task when native iOS code is touched anyway.

## Drift table definitions (lib/src/database/tables.dart)

```dart
class TodoListsTable extends Table {
  @override String get tableName => 'todo_lists';

  TextColumn get id => text()();
  TextColumn get title => text()();
  IntColumn get color => integer().withDefault(const Constant(0xFF2196F3))();
  BoolColumn get notifyOnEnter => boolean().withDefault(const Constant(true))();
  BoolColumn get notifyOnExit => boolean().withDefault(const Constant(false))();
  TextColumn get geofenceId => text().nullable()();
  IntColumn get sortOrder => integer().withDefault(const Constant(0))();
  DateTimeColumn get createdAt => dateTime()();

  @override Set<Column> get primaryKey => {id};
}

class TodoItemsTable extends Table {
  @override String get tableName => 'todo_items';

  TextColumn get id => text()();
  TextColumn get listId => text().references(TodoListsTable, #id, onDelete: KeyAction.cascade)();
  TextColumn get title => text()();
  TextColumn get notes => text().nullable()();
  BoolColumn get isDone => boolean().withDefault(const Constant(false))();
  DateTimeColumn get dueDate => dateTime().nullable()();
  IntColumn get priority => integer().withDefault(const Constant(0))();

  @override Set<Column> get primaryKey => {id};
}

class GeofenceRegionsTable extends Table {
  @override String get tableName => 'geofence_regions';

  TextColumn get id => text()();
  RealColumn get latitude => real()();
  RealColumn get longitude => real()();
  RealColumn get radiusMeters => real()();
  TextColumn get label => text().withDefault(const Constant(''))();
  BoolColumn get isActive => boolean().withDefault(const Constant(true))();
  TextColumn get trigger => text().withDefault(const Constant('enter'))();
  DateTimeColumn get createdAt => dateTime()();

  @override Set<Column> get primaryKey => {id};
}
```

Add a custom index (in the `AppDatabase.onCreate` or via drift `@TableIndex`):
`CREATE INDEX idx_todo_items_list_done ON todo_items(list_id, is_done)`

## Repository implementations (lib/src/repositories/)

### DriftTodoListRepository (implements TodoListRepository)
```
getAllLists()            → SELECT * FROM todo_lists ORDER BY sort_order ASC
watchAllLists()          → SELECT ... watch()
getListById(id)          → SELECT WHERE id = ? (returns null if not found)
getListByGeofenceId(id)  → SELECT WHERE geofence_id = ? (returns null if not found) ← NEW
saveList(list)           → insertOnConflictUpdate (upsert by primary key)
deleteList(id)           → DELETE WHERE id = ?
```

### DriftTodoItemRepository (implements TodoItemRepository)
```
getItemsForList(listId)        → SELECT WHERE list_id = ? ORDER BY priority DESC, is_done ASC
watchItemsForList(listId)      → SELECT ... watch()
getItemById(id)                → SELECT WHERE id = ? (returns null if not found) ← NEW
saveItem(item)                 → insertOnConflictUpdate
deleteItem(id)                 → DELETE WHERE id = ?
countIncompleteItems(listId)   → SELECT COUNT(*) WHERE list_id = ? AND is_done = 0
```

### DriftGeofenceRepository (implements GeofenceRepository)
```
getGeofenceById(id)           → SELECT WHERE id = ?
getAllActiveGeofences()        → SELECT WHERE is_active = 1
saveGeofence(region)          → insertOnConflictUpdate
deleteGeofence(id)            → DELETE WHERE id = ?
setGeofenceActive(id, active) → UPDATE SET is_active = ? WHERE id = ? ← NEW
```

## Data mappers (lib/src/mappers/)
Provide extension methods on each drift row type to convert to/from domain entities:

```dart
extension TodoListRowMapper on TodoListsTableData {
  TodoList toDomain() => TodoList(
    id: id, title: title, color: color,
    notifyOnEnter: notifyOnEnter, notifyOnExit: notifyOnExit,
    geofenceId: geofenceId, sortOrder: sortOrder, createdAt: createdAt,
  );
}

extension TodoListDomainMapper on TodoList {
  TodoListsTableCompanion toCompanion() => TodoListsTableCompanion(
    id: Value(id), title: Value(title), ...
  );
}
```
(Same pattern for TodoItem and GeofenceRegion.)

