## Overview
Implement the `packages/domain` package: all domain entities, repository interfaces (abstractions), and use cases. This is a pure Dart package with zero external dependencies except `equatable`.

## Depends on
- while-youre-out-qys (monorepo scaffold must exist first)

## Package location
`packages/domain/`

## Key dependencies (pubspec.yaml)
```yaml
dependencies:
  equatable: ^2.0.5
  uuid: ^4.0.0
dev_dependencies:
  very_good_analysis: ^5.1.0
  mocktail: ^1.0.0
  test: ^1.24.0
```
Note: `uuid` is used inside use cases to generate IDs; `equatable` for value equality on entities.

## Entities (lib/src/entities/)
Create immutable value objects. Each must extend `Equatable` (or have manual `==`/`hashCode`), and include a `copyWith` method.

```dart
// TodoList
class TodoList extends Equatable {
  const TodoList({
    required this.id,
    required this.title,
    this.color = 0xFF2196F3,
    this.notifyOnEnter = true,
    this.notifyOnExit = false,
    this.geofenceId,
    required this.sortOrder,
    required this.createdAt,
  });
  final String id;       // UUID
  final String title;
  final int color;       // ARGB int (matches Flutter Color.value)
  final bool notifyOnEnter;
  final bool notifyOnExit;
  final String? geofenceId;  // nullable FK to GeofenceRegion
  final int sortOrder;
  final DateTime createdAt;
  TodoList copyWith({...});
  @override List<Object?> get props => [id, title, color, ...];
}

// TodoItem
class TodoItem extends Equatable {
  const TodoItem({required this.id, required this.listId, required this.title, ...});
  final String id;
  final String listId;
  final String title;
  final String? notes;
  final bool isDone;
  final DateTime? dueDate;
  final int priority;     // 0=none, 1=low, 2=medium, 3=high
  TodoItem copyWith({...});
  @override List<Object?> get props => [...];
}

// GeofenceRegion
class GeofenceRegion extends Equatable {
  final String id;
  final double latitude;
  final double longitude;
  final double radiusMeters;  // minimum enforced at use-case level: 100m
  final String label;
  final bool isActive;
  final GeofenceTrigger trigger;
  final DateTime createdAt;
  GeofenceRegion copyWith({...});
  @override List<Object?> get props => [...];
}

enum GeofenceTrigger { enter, exit, enterAndExit }

// GeofenceEvent — fired by the OS via GeofenceService.events stream
class GeofenceEvent extends Equatable {
  const GeofenceEvent({
    required this.regionId,
    required this.type,
    required this.timestamp,
  });
  final String regionId;
  final GeofenceEventType type;
  final DateTime timestamp;
  @override List<Object?> get props => [regionId, type, timestamp];
}

enum GeofenceEventType { enter, exit }
```

## Repository interfaces (lib/src/repositories/)
Abstract classes implemented by the `data` package:

```dart
abstract class TodoListRepository {
  Future<List<TodoList>> getAllLists();
  Stream<List<TodoList>> watchAllLists();        // reactive — for UI
  Future<TodoList?> getListById(String id);
  Future<TodoList?> getListByGeofenceId(String geofenceId);  // used by HandleGeofenceEntryUseCase
  Future<void> saveList(TodoList list);
  Future<void> deleteList(String id);
}

abstract class TodoItemRepository {
  Future<List<TodoItem>> getItemsForList(String listId);
  Stream<List<TodoItem>> watchItemsForList(String listId);
  Future<TodoItem?> getItemById(String id);  // needed by ToggleItemUseCase to fetch before flip
  Future<void> saveItem(TodoItem item);
  Future<void> deleteItem(String id);
  Future<int> countIncompleteItems(String listId);  // for dashboard badge
}

abstract class GeofenceRepository {
  Future<GeofenceRegion?> getGeofenceById(String id);
  Future<List<GeofenceRegion>> getAllActiveGeofences();
  Future<void> saveGeofence(GeofenceRegion region);
  Future<void> deleteGeofence(String id);
  Future<void> setGeofenceActive(String id, {required bool active});  // used by RefreshActiveGeofencesUseCase
}
```

## OS service interfaces (lib/src/services/)
Abstract classes implemented by `geofencing` and `notifications` packages:

```dart
abstract class GeofenceService {
  Future<void> registerRegion(GeofenceRegion region);
  Future<void> unregisterRegion(String regionId);
  Future<void> unregisterAll();
  Stream<GeofenceEvent> get events;
}

abstract class NotificationService {
  Future<void> initialize();
  Future<void> postListNotification({
    required String listId,
    required String listTitle,
    required int incompleteCount,
  });
  Future<bool> requestPermission();
}
```

## Use cases (lib/src/use_cases/)
Each use case is a class with a single `call` method. Inject all dependencies via constructor.

| Class | Constructor deps | call() signature | Logic |
|---|---|---|---|
| `CreateListUseCase` | TodoListRepository | `Future<TodoList> call({required String title, int color = 0xFF2196F3})` | Generate UUID via `const Uuid().v4()`, set sortOrder = (max existing sortOrder) + 1, call saveList |
| `DeleteListUseCase` | TodoListRepository, TodoItemRepository, GeofenceRepository, GeofenceService | `Future<void> call(String listId)` | Load list; if geofenceId != null: unregisterRegion + deleteGeofence; delete all items for list; deleteList |
| `AssignLocationUseCase` | TodoListRepository, GeofenceRepository | `Future<void> call({required String listId, required double lat, required double lng, required double radiusMeters, String label = ''})` | If list already has geofenceId, overwrite that record; else create new GeofenceRegion with new UUID; saveGeofence; update list.geofenceId; saveList |
| `RegisterGeofenceUseCase` | GeofenceRepository, GeofenceService | `Future<void> call(String geofenceId)` | Load GeofenceRegion; call service.registerRegion; setGeofenceActive(true) |
| `UnregisterGeofenceUseCase` | GeofenceRepository, GeofenceService | `Future<void> call(String geofenceId)` | service.unregisterRegion; setGeofenceActive(false) |
| `ToggleItemUseCase` | TodoItemRepository | `Future<TodoItem> call(String itemId)` | getItemById; item.copyWith(isDone: !item.isDone); saveItem; return updated item |
| `ReorderListsUseCase` | TodoListRepository | `Future<void> call(List<String> orderedIds)` | For each id at index i: load list, list.copyWith(sortOrder: i), saveList |
| `HandleGeofenceEntryUseCase` | TodoListRepository, TodoItemRepository, NotificationService | `Future<void> call(String regionId)` | getListByGeofenceId(regionId); if null return; countIncompleteItems; postListNotification |
| `RefreshActiveGeofencesUseCase` | GeofenceRepository, GeofenceService | `Future<void> call({required double currentLat, required double currentLng})` | getAllActiveGeofences(); sort by haversine distance asc; take first 20 → registerRegion; remainder → unregisterRegion + setGeofenceActive(false) |
| `CreateItemUseCase` | TodoItemRepository | `Future<TodoItem> call({required String listId, required String title, String? notes, int priority = 0})` | Generate UUID; saveItem; return |
| `DeleteItemUseCase` | TodoItemRepository | `Future<void> call(String itemId)` | deleteItem |

### Haversine helper
Add a private `_haversineDistance(double lat1, double lon1, double lat2, double lon2) → double` function (returns meters) in `RefreshActiveGeofencesUseCase` — do NOT import dart:math in entities; keep it in the use case file only.

