## iOS Priority Queue: GeofenceManager (apps/mobile/lib/geofence_manager.dart)

The GeofenceManager lives in `apps/mobile` (not the geofencing package) because it depends on `RefreshActiveGeofencesUseCase` which is a domain use case — it's the app-layer orchestrator.

```dart
class GeofenceManager {
  GeofenceManager({
    required this.geofenceService,
    required this.refreshActiveGeofences,
  });

  final GeofenceService geofenceService;
  final RefreshActiveGeofencesUseCase refreshActiveGeofences;
  StreamSubscription<Position>? _locationSub;

  void start() {
    // Only activate on iOS — on Android all 100 geofences can stay registered
    if (!Platform.isIOS) return;

    _locationSub = Geolocator.getPositionStream(
      locationSettings: const LocationSettings(
        distanceFilter: 500,  // fire every 500m of movement
        accuracy: LocationAccuracy.low,  // conserve battery
      ),
    ).listen((position) async {
      await refreshActiveGeofences(
        currentLat: position.latitude,
        currentLng: position.longitude,
      );
    });
  }

  void dispose() => _locationSub?.cancel();
}
```

Instantiate in `apps/mobile/lib/main.dart` and call `geofenceManager.start()` after DI setup. Use `Geolocator` (already in `apps/mobile` pubspec from while-youre-out-qys).

